-- German Companies Contribute $1.7 Million to U.S. Candidates, Welt Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2010-10-22T06:07:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/german-companies-contribute-1-7-million-to-u-s-candidates-welt-reports.html
German companies including Bayer AG
have pumped $1.7 million into U.S. political campaigns ahead of
the Nov. 2 elections, the  Die Welt  newspaper reported.  The main contributors to campaigns are large companies with
U.S. units, the newspaper said, citing the Federal Election
Commission. The 50 biggest German companies employ 300,000 in
the U.S., the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Brian Parkin  in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  